-- New Jersey to Halt All State-Funded Transportation Construction Projects
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 2010-10-01T19:39:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/new-jersey-to-halt-state-backed-transportation-projects-on-lack-of-funding.html
New Jersey Department of
Transportation Commissioner James Simpson said he is halting
all state-funded transportation construction projects effective
Oct 4. Simpson said he was taking the action because the state
Legislature did not approve a bond sale to fund previously
authorized work.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  